msgid "Functionality added or changed"
msgstr "Изменения или добавления функциональности"

msgid "Core"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Now it is allowed to define an index without extra braces when there is only"
" one part: ``parts = {field1, type1, ...}`` (:tarantool-issue:`2866`). Read "
"more in the :ref:`note about index parts declaration "
"<index_parts_declaration_note>`."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
":ref:`Bitset index <indexes-bitset>` now supports the varbinary type "
"(:tarantool-issue:`5392`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Index-related options now can’t be specified in their definition due to a "
"more pedantic key-parts verification (:tarantool-issue:`5473`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"A warning is now logged when schema version is older than last available "
"schema version (:tarantool-issue:`4574`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"UUID values created via ``uuid`` Lua module (``require('uuid')``) can now be"
" compared using the comparison operators like ``<``, ``>=``, and others "
"(:tarantool-issue:`5511`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The new ``box.ctl.is_recovery_finished()`` function allows user to determine"
" whether memtx recovery is finished."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The ``force_recovery`` option now ignores errors during snapshot recovery "
"(:tarantool-issue:`5422`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Feedback daemon now reports ``box.stat().*.total``, "
"``box.stat.net().*.total``, and ``box.stat.net().*.current`` together with "
"the time of report generation. The added fields reside in "
"``feedback.stats.box``, ``feedback.stats.net``, and ``feedback.stats.time`` "
"(:tarantool-issue:`5589`)."
msgstr ""

